    <section id="id7354389">
      <title>The senses of smell and taste</title>
      <para id="id7354396"/>
      <para id="id7354400">Activity: To learn more about the senses of smell and taste [LO 2.1]</para>
      <para id="id7354412">When you eat, the tongue tastes the taste of the food and your nose smells the flavour. This is how it works:</para>
      <para id="id8105709">The openings of your mouth and nose come together in your throat, behind your mouth. The flavours of the food that you eat go to your nose from the back of your mouth. From there, nerves take a message to the brain and the brain tells you what you smell.</para>
